---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout pageKey="rooftop-solar-lucknow.html" headerVariant="guide">

<!-- HERO -->

<section class="py-20">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">

<div class="inline-block bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold">
Local Solar Guide · Lucknow, Uttar Pradesh
</div>

<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mt-6">
Rooftop Solar in Lucknow
</h1>

<p class="text-slate-600 text-lg mt-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
Lucknow homeowners are reducing MVVNL electricity bills with rooftop solar and PM Surya Ghar subsidies.
This guide covers everything — costs, net metering, empanelled installers, and how to get started.
</p>

<a href="index.html"
   class="inline-block mt-8 bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold transition">
  Check My Solar Savings
</a>

</div>
</section>

<!-- QUICK FACTS -->

<section class="pb-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-5">

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border">
<div class="text-sm text-slate-500">DISCOM</div>
<div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">MVVNL</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Madhyanchal / UPPCL</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border">
<div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Avg Sun Hours</div>
<div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">5–5.5 hrs/day</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Annual average</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border">
<div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Central Subsidy</div>
<div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">For 3kW · verify at portal</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border">
<div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Typical Payback</div>
<div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-indigo-700">4–6 Years</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">After subsidy</div>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- WHY SOLAR IN LUCKNOW -->

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Why Rooftop Solar Makes Sense in Lucknow</h2>

<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">High Solar Irradiance</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
Lucknow receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours daily on average — well above
the national minimum for financially viable rooftop solar. Long, intense summers mean
panels generate at near-peak output for several months of the year.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Summer Bills & Solar Output Align</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
Lucknow summers drive significant air conditioning use — exactly when solar panels
generate the most electricity. Your biggest MVVNL bills coincide with your highest
solar output, making the financial case stronger than in many other cities.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Rising MVVNL Tariffs</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
MVVNL domestic electricity tariffs have increased over successive regulatory revisions.
Locking in solar generation now insulates your household from future tariff hikes —
every unit you generate is a unit you do not pay retail rates for.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">PM Surya Ghar Opportunity</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
Lucknow homeowners with an MVVNL connection are eligible for the PM Surya Ghar Muft
Bijli Yojana central subsidy. Uttar Pradesh is among the leading states for scheme uptake,
and MVVNL has an active list of empanelled installers across Lucknow.
</p>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- MVVNL NET METERING PROCESS -->

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">MVVNL Net Metering in Lucknow</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">How the net metering connection process works for Lucknow homeowners under MVVNL.</p>

<div class="space-y-4">

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start">
<div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</div>
<div>
<h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Install via MVVNL-Empanelled Installer</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Your installer must be registered and empanelled with MVVNL under the PM Surya Ghar scheme.
Verify empanelment status on pmsuryaghar.gov.in before signing any contract.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start">
<div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</div>
<div>
<h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Submit Net Metering Application to MVVNL</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">After installation, your installer submits the net metering application to MVVNL with technical
details of the system. Most reputable installers handle this paperwork on your behalf.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start">
<div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</div>
<div>
<h3 class="font-bold mb-1">MVVNL Technical Inspection</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">An MVVNL engineer visits your premises to inspect the installation for grid safety compliance.
This typically takes two to four weeks in Lucknow, depending on workload.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start">
<div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">4</div>
<div>
<h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Bi-Directional Meter Installation</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Your existing MVVNL meter is replaced with a net meter capable of measuring both import from
and export to the grid. There may be a one-time meter replacement fee charged by MVVNL.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start">
<div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">5</div>
<div>
<h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Commissioning & Net Metering Active</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Once the meter is installed, MVVNL officially commissions your system. From this point,
surplus solar exported to the grid earns credits on your monthly MVVNL bill.</p>
</div>
</div>

</div>

<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-6">
Total process: typically two to six weeks from application to active net metering in Lucknow.
Your installer should guide you through each step. See our
<a href="learn/net-metering-india.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">net metering guide</a>
for a full explanation of how credits work on your bill.
</p>

</div>
</section>

<!-- SYSTEM SIZES FOR LUCKNOW -->

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Choosing the Right System Size in Lucknow</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Match your monthly MVVNL bill to the right system size.</p>

<div class="overflow-x-auto">
<table class="w-full text-sm bg-white rounded-2xl border overflow-hidden">
<thead class="bg-slate-50">
<tr>
<th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Monthly MVVNL Bill</th>
<th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Recommended Size</th>
<th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Roof Area Needed</th>
<th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Best For</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
<tr>
<td class="p-4">₹1,000 – ₹2,500</td>
<td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="2kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">2kW System</a></td>
<td class="p-4">160–220 sq ft</td>
<td class="p-4">Small families, 2BHK flats</td>
</tr>
<tr class="bg-emerald-50">
<td class="p-4">₹2,500 – ₹5,000</td>
<td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="3kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">3kW System</a> ★ Most popular</td>
<td class="p-4">240–300 sq ft</td>
<td class="p-4">Medium families, 3BHK homes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="p-4">₹4,000 – ₹7,000</td>
<td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="5kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">5kW System</a></td>
<td class="p-4">400–500 sq ft</td>
<td class="p-4">Larger homes, heavy AC use</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="p-4">₹7,000+</td>
<td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="10kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">10kW System</a></td>
<td class="p-4">800–1,000 sq ft</td>
<td class="p-4">Large bungalows, kothi</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>

<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-4">
Sizes are indicative. Actual recommendation depends on roof orientation, shading, and consumption profile.
Use our <a href="learn/solar-system-sizing-guide.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">solar system sizing guide</a>
to understand the full methodology.
</p>

</div>
</section>

<!-- PM SURYA GHAR IN LUCKNOW -->

<section class="py-12 bg-emerald-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">PM Surya Ghar Subsidy in Lucknow</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">
Lucknow homeowners with an MVVNL electricity connection can apply for the PM Surya Ghar
Muft Bijli Yojana central subsidy through the official portal.
</p>

<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Up to 2kW</div>
<div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">₹30,000/kW</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Central subsidy · verify at portal</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">3kW System Total</div>
<div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">3rd kW subsidised at lower rate</div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Above 3kW</div>
<div class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-700">No central subsidy</div>
<div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Beyond 3kW capacity</div>
</div>

</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold mb-3">How to Apply as a Lucknow Homeowner</h3>
<ol class="space-y-2 text-slate-700 text-sm">
<li>1. Register at <strong>pmsuryaghar.gov.in</strong> using your MVVNL consumer number</li>
<li>2. Select an MVVNL-empanelled installer from the portal's installer list</li>
<li>3. Get the system installed, net metering connected, and MVVNL commissioning done</li>
<li>4. Complete the subsidy disbursement application on the portal</li>
<li>5. Subsidy credited directly to your bank account — typically within weeks to months</li>
</ol>
<p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-4">
Subsidy amounts and eligibility criteria are subject to government policy and fund availability.
Always verify current rates on the official portal before making financial decisions.
</p>
</div>

<div class="mt-4">
<a href="learn/pm-surya-ghar-guide.html" class="inline-flex items-center text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline text-sm">
Read the full PM Surya Ghar guide →
</a>
</div>

</div>
</section>

<!-- NEIGHBOURHOODS -->

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Lucknow Areas We Serve</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">
We help homeowners across Lucknow understand their solar options and connect with
verified, MVVNL-empanelled installers in their area.
</p>

<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
{[
  "Gomti Nagar", "Hazratganj", "Indira Nagar", "Aliganj", "Alambagh",
  "Mahanagar", "Vikas Nagar", "Chinhat", "Jankipuram", "Kalyanpur",
  "Sushant Golf City", "Vrindavan Yojana", "Sultanpur Road", "Faizabad Road",
  "Rajajipuram", "Ashiyana", "Telibagh", "Sarojini Nagar"
].map(area => (
  <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-slate-100 rounded-full text-sm text-slate-700 font-medium">{area}</span>
))}
</div>

</div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions — Lucknow Solar</h2>

<div class="space-y-4">

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">Which electricity company handles rooftop solar in Lucknow?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
Lucknow falls under <strong>MVVNL (Madhyanchal Vidyut Vitran Nigam Limited)</strong>, a subsidiary
of UPPCL. All net metering applications, bi-directional meter installations, and solar scheme
empanelment for Lucknow homeowners are processed through MVVNL.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">How do I apply for net metering with MVVNL in Lucknow?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
After installation by an MVVNL-empanelled installer, your installer submits a net metering
application to MVVNL. MVVNL inspects the system and replaces your meter with a bi-directional
net meter. The full process typically takes two to six weeks in Lucknow.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">Is PM Surya Ghar subsidy available in Lucknow?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
Yes. Lucknow homeowners with an MVVNL electricity connection are eligible. You must use an
MVVNL-empanelled installer and apply through pmsuryaghar.gov.in. Subsidy amounts are subject
to government policy and current fund availability — verify before applying.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">What solar system size suits most Lucknow homes?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
For typical Lucknow residential homes with monthly MVVNL bills of ₹2,000–₹5,000, a 2kW to 3kW
on-grid system covers a significant portion of electricity needs. Homes with heavy summer AC use
often find a 3kW or 5kW system more appropriate.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">How much does rooftop solar cost in Lucknow?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
Approximate pre-subsidy cost for a quality on-grid system in Lucknow ranges from ₹60,000 to
₹80,000 per kW, varying by panel brand, inverter type, and installer. After the PM Surya Ghar
central subsidy (up to ₹78,000 for 3kW), net cost is significantly lower. Always get quotes from
at least two MVVNL-empanelled installers.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">Is Lucknow a good location for rooftop solar?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
Yes. Lucknow receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours per day on average — well suited for
rooftop solar. Intense summers mean high solar output coincides with peak electricity demand,
making solar financially effective for most Lucknow homeowners.
</p>
</div>

</div>

</div>
</section>

